QUESTIONS FOR THE DEFENDANT INTENDING TO PLEAD GUILTY

1. If I ask something that you do not understand, please ask me to explain it and/or repeat it. Do you understand this?

2. You have the right to an attorney. You attorney(s) may represent you at all stages of a criminal proceeding. If you cannot afford an attorney, the Court will appoint one for you at no cost. Do you understand this?

3. If you have an attorney, have you discussed this case in its entirety with your attorney?

4. If you have an attorney, have you discussed the stipulations and any possible consequences of the plea deal with your attorney?

5. If you have an attorney, are you confident in the advice provided by them?

6. The decision to enter a plea of guilty must be your own, not your attorney's. Do you understand this?

7. By pleading guilty, you are admitting guilt that you committed the specified crimes in the plea bargain agreement. Do you understand this?
krabzatonin 2025-01-02 02:47 a.m.
REQUIREMENTS UNDER MAYFL. R. CRIM. P. 5(5)(1)

8. Mayfl. R. Crim. P. 5(5)(1)(1):The Criminal Information brought before the Court accuses you of committing 1 M.S.C. § 2302 "Assault with a deadly weapon," 1 M.S.C. § 2306 "Felony hit and run," 2 M.S.C. § 1213 "Felony Reckless Driving," and 2 M.S.C. § 1212 "Reckless Driving," as Counts One, Two, Three, and Four respectively. Count One carries a sentence of 25 minutes. Count Two carries a sentence of 20 minutes. Count Three carries a sentence of 15 minutes, and/or a $780 fine. Count 4 carries a sentence of 10 minutes, and/or a $250 fine. Do you understand the sentences and fines for all four counts in the Information?

9. Mayfl. R. Crim. P. 5(5)(1)(2): The recommendation of the prosecuting attorney as to punishment is not binding on the Court. If the Court decides to reject the plea bargain agreement, you are entitled to withdraw your plea of guilty. For the record, the Court will follow the terms of the plea bargain agreement. Do you understand this?

10. Mayfl. R. Crim. P. 5(5)(1)(3): If the punishment assessed does not exceed the punishment recommended by the prosecutor and agreed to by you and your attorney, the Court must give you its permission before you may prosecute an appeal on any matter in this case, except for matters raised by written motions filed prior to trial. Do you understand this?

FINAL QUESTIONS

11. Do you feel mentally competent right now?

12. The Court will dismiss, with prejudice, Counts One and Four of the Information if you enter a plea of guilty. Do you understand this?

13. Consult your attorney(s) before you answer this question: how do you plead to Counts Two and Three the Criminal Information filed with the Court (1 M.S.C. § 2306 "Felony hit and run" and 2 M.S.C. § 1213 "Felony Reckless Driving.")?(edited)
